reviews.review_text: As an Indian Classical musician, I have been tirelessly working through sitting cross legged and playing my tabla for over 10 hours a day for 30 + years. Needless to say, both Professional Hazard and age has caught up to me and I need intense physiotherapy for my neck, shoulders, arms, hips and legs. Basically, a full overhaul of my joints, ligaments and muscles. I came to see my dear friend Krishna Jeeja at her MJ Physio clinic on Fraser St and 41st in Vancouver and started my treatment. I was quite nervous as asides from the few massages I have had with my wife at couples spas I have never been to any sort of therapy in this regard. Krishna completely made me feel at ease, explaining to me the details of my therapy and what was required. She made correct analysis on all of my problem joints in my body and exactly described my pain as if it was me talking. She is very knowledgeable on the workings of the human body. I feel an intense decrease in pain ever since Krishna started treating me, as a matter of fact I feel much better now than I have in years though I am aware it will take more than a few sessions to correct my body alignment. As I have been having intense pain in my ankle bones as well as my shoulders and neck Krishna was very quick in identifying the problem as bursitis. I assumed that only cortisol can treat this pain but I was hesitant of ever getting that treatment done. After Krishna told me they treat bursitis through laser  I am looking forward to getting laser treatment done in their Surrey location. I will recommend this place to anyone in need of physio. Krishna is kind hearted, professional, direct and an absolute joy to talk to. She is friendly and makes you feel at ease. Their facility has a nice gym, state of the art equipment and a very friendly receptionist. For the first time in my life I feel that I will get better and continue my work in music. Thank you Krishna and thank you MJ Physio for being there- and thank you for supporting the Arts in our city ( MJ Physio is one of our major sponsors for our Mushtari Begum Festival of Indian Classical Music and Dance) and selflessly donating your time to our Vancouver community. I give you 6/5 stars!

reviews.review_text: Sometimes soft tissue injuries makes big impact in your lifestyle. I am in rehabilitation phase of my tendonitis  and I needed a structured plan to strengthen my tissues and improve flexibility to the muscles to get back the sports activities. Dr. Ram carefully evaluated my injury and  planned out a work out regime and strengthening exercises using the facilities of the fraser street MJ Physio clinic. I could see a considerable difference over the period of time. Apart from exceptional planning and monitoring my rehab , the infrastructure available in the clinic accelerated the progress. All credits to Dr.Ram and Jeeja for their dedication and approach . Congratulations and keep up the good work.
